title: China Southern Airlines donates 4000 medical gloves to Perlis State Government in Malaysia.
description: On April 8, 2020. China Southern Airlines donated 5000 medical gloves to State Government to help its effort to fight against Covid-19. On the same day, the Chinese Consulate General in Penang also provided a donation of 15,000 masks to the Perlis State Government in Malaysia.
staff_comments: AidData has estimated the transaction amount for this donation based on price catalogues from the World Health Organization (WHO). Please see the TUFF Methodology for additional details.
combined_text:

# Description
On April 8, 2020. China Southern Airlines donated 5000 medical gloves to State Government to help its effort to fight against Covid-19. On the same day, the Chinese Consulate General in Penang also provided a donation of 15,000 masks to the Perlis State Government in Malaysia.
justification: Project is a donation of medical supplies unrelated to energy or environmental impacts
evidence: Donation of medical gloves and masks for COVID-19 response

title: Chinese Embassy in Malaysia donate Covid-19 supplies to Malaysia Ministry of Health (Linked to #93888)
description: On March 24, 2020, Chinese Ambassador Bai Tian donated 5,000 N95 masks, 20,000 medical masks, and 1,200 protection goggles on behalf of the Chinese Embassy and China Communications Construction Company to the Malaysian Ministry of Health to fight against Covid-19.  The contribution from the China Communications Construction Company is captured via Project #93888.
staff_comments: 1. Because the Chinese Embassy and China Communications Construction Company both contributed an unknown number of supplies to this donation, AidData assumes each donor made an equal contribution. The total value of the donation is estimated to be $33,100.00, with each donor contributing an estimated USD 16,550.00 (USD 33,100.00 / 2 known contributors = USD 16,550.00).
combined_text:

The monetary value of the donation is unknown.
staff_comments: 1. The total value of the donation is estimated to be $420,000.00, with each donor contributing an estimated USD 70,000.00 (USD 420,000.00 / 6 known contributors = USD 70,000.00).

title: Bornion Guangken Rubber, Chinese General Consulate in Kota Kinabalu and other Chinese enterprises donate Covid-19 supplies to Sabah State Government in Malaysia (Linked to Project ID#93913, 93914, 93915, 90240)
description: On March 29, 2020, the Chinese Consulate General in Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia (Project ID#90240), together with China State Construction Engineering (M) Sdn Bhd (Project ID#93915), China Railway Dongfang Group Sdn Bhd (Project ID#93914), Sinohydro Corporation (M) Sdn Bhd (Project ID#93913), and Bornion Guangken Rubber Sdn Bhd (Project ID#93912) donated 166,000 masks and other supplies like goggles and protective suits to the Sabah State Government in Malaysia. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.  In early April, the Chinese Consulate General donated 20,000 masks from this batch of supplies to Sabah State Immigration Bureau, Kota Kinabalu's Municipal Government, the police department, and Hospital Wanita Dan Kanak-Kanak Sabah and Queen Elizabeth Hospital.
staff_comments: 1. Bornion Guangken Rubber Sdn Bhd is a 50/50 Joint Venture between Guangdong Guangken Rubber Group and Bornion Timber Sdn Bhd2. Because China State Construction Engineering Sdn Bhd, China Railway Dongfang Group Sdn Bhd, Sinohydro Corporation Sdn Bhd, Bornion Guangken Rubber Sdn Bhd, and the Chinese Consulate General in Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia all contributed an unknown number of supplies to this donation, AidData assumes each donor made an equal contribution. The total value of the donation is estimated to be $116,200, with each donor contributing USD 23,240 (USD 116,200 / 5 known contributors = USD 23,240).
combined_text:

HEALTH
